QA Sr Mgr job
in Singapore
Job Ref:
23077BR
COUNTRY:
Singapore
CITY:
Singapore
EMPLOYER:
INDUSTRY:
Quality Assurance
This position will independently manage the Quality relationship and oversight of distributors and packaging contractors in the Asia region (excluding Japan and China) to ensure compliance with local regulations, Amgen policies, standards and procedures.
The role of the QA Senior Manager will include the following:
• Maintain and manage the Quality Agreement with the distributor and actively review periodically • Develop and implement Amgen Quality Management System (QMS) processes. • Act as the Quality Responsible Person in accordance to local regulations, as required • Manage CQC Audits and ensure responses to findings are submitted and completed on time. • Perform technical assessments and audits of local laboratories, warehouses and packaging facilities. • Coordinate transfer of analytical methods to country laboratories, as required. • Develop reports and provide the necessary communications throughout the organizations. • Lead cross-functional teams that include both internal and external participation. • Participate as a core team member in product launch teams and product licensing for region. • Continuously monitor GMP/GDP regulations, guidance and trends for the region
This position is based in Singapore, with likelihood of high level of travel in the region. label • Doctorate degree and 2 years of directly related experience or Master's degree and 6 years of directly related experience or Bachelor's degree and 8 years of directly related experience or Associate's degree and 10 years of directly related experience. • Ability to work independently and manage multiple priorities at one time • Effective communicator (written and oral) in English label • Self-motivated, resilient individual with strong knowledge of Quality Management processes and International GMPs and Good Distribution Practices (GDPs) • Cultural dexterity and regional languages skills • Previous experience managing distributors • Able to interpret and apply quality and compliance requirements • Able to work independently as well as on teams • Able to work in a challenging and fast-paced work environment • Understands cross functional interdependencies and its impact in the operation; i.e. Quality, Regulatory Affairs, Supply Chain, Manufacturing Sites and Commercial • Demonstrated skills in leading, influencing, and negotiating • Excellent verbal and written communication skills, including technical writing • Ability to effectively interact with various levels.
Post Date:
04/28/2014
